# WHAT IT IS
#   pullsheet generates CSV / HTML / JSON / spreadsheet
#   summaries of GitHub contribution activity across one or
#   more orgs / repos / branches / users / date ranges.  Use
#   cases:  quarterly OKR reporting, per-engineer review-load
#   tracking, cross-repo bus-factor analysis, OSS-grant
#   recipient activity reports, conference-speaker submission
#   gating ("hey, you said you were active in the project
#   — show me the data"), and the kind of "who reviewed how
#   many PRs in 2026 Q3" question that historically required
#   bespoke scripts.
#
#   Five reporting modes:
#     • `prs`             — pull requests authored
#     • `issues`          — issues authored
#     • `issue-comments`  — comments on issues
#     • `reviews`         — pull-request review activity
#     • `leaderboard`     — per-user totals across all axes
#                          (also exposed via the `server`
#                          subcommand as a live web UI)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/root.go +
#                       cmd/{issues-comments,issues,leader
#                       board,prs,review,server}.go cobra +
#                       pflag declarations; extracted via
#                       `gh api repos/google/pullsheet/
#                       contents/cmd/...`)
#
#   pullsheet [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND>
#
#   Global persistent flags  (every subcommand):
#     --org <NAME>                   GitHub org name (scope
#                                    queries to this org's
#                                    public repos)
#     --repos <REPO,REPO>            Comma-delimited list of
#                                    repositories
#                                    (e.g.
#                                    `kubernetes/minikube,
#                                    google/pullsheet`)
#     --branches <BRANCH,BRANCH>     Comma-delimited list of
#                                    branches (e.g.
#                                    `master,main,head`)
#     --users <USER,USER>            Comma-delimited list of
#                                    GitHub usernames
#     --since <TIME>                 When to query from (date
#                                    or duration)
#                                    [default: now-90d]
#     --until <TIME>                 When to query till (date
#                                    or duration)
#                                    [default: now]
#     --include-bots                 Include bot accounts in
#                                    the output
#                                    [default: false]
#     --title <TITLE>                Title to use for output
#                                    pages
#     --token-path <PATH>            GitHub token file path
#                                    (alternative to
#                                    GITHUB_TOKEN env)
#     --out <FORMAT>                 Output format
#                                    [default: CSV]
#                                    (CSV | HTML | JSON,
#                                    plus per-subcommand
#                                    variants)
#
#   Subcommands:
#     prs                            Generate data around pull
#                                    requests
#     issues                         Generate data around
#                                    issues
#     issue-comments                 Generate data around
#                                    comments on issues
#     reviews                        Generate data around
#                                    reviews
#     leaderboard                    Generate leaderboard data
#                                    (per-user totals across
#                                    all axes)
#     server                         Serve leaderboard data
#                                    with web UI
#
#   Standard cobra auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
